description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whipps Cross Paediatric Assessment Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Is your passion giving excellent care to sick children whatever their diagnosis?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you career minded with drive and enthusiasm?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you enjoy playing a key role in a multidisciplinary team in acute care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, we are currently recruiting for RSCN/RN child branch Ward Manager to join our dynamic friendly Paediatric team to run our newly designed Paediatric Assessment Unit (PAU)at Whipps Cross Hospital, Leytonstone site due to open November 2020. The PAU will be operational Mon to Fri 10:00-22:30. This is a fixed term post until the end of March 2021 and the hours of work will be 10:00-18:00 Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Whipps Cross Children’s unit is a growing team who serves a diverse population and care for children and young people admitted with acute nursing and medical needs aged 0-16 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Renowned for their friendly, welcoming, “can do” approach, the Paediatric team care for children and young people with both short term illnesses and injuries, and those who require longer term support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate will have acute post registration Paediatric experience. You will need to have the skills and abilities to deliver high standards of care and have the resilience to meet the challenges of our busy and stimulating work environment. You should be self-motivated, an excellent communicator and have proven clinical and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for your next role and an opportunity, where you can quickly make a difference in Paediatric Care, then we would be pleased to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barts Health has a multi-cultural and ethnically diverse population. This offers a wide spectrum of healthcare challenges which can be both complex and rewarding. As part of our commitment to improve the working lives of our staff, we offer flexible working arrangements, childcare vouchers, family-friendly policies and staff benefits including an excellent pension scheme. We are committed to providing a culture of continuous learning, which actively supports the professional and personal development of our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we aim to have health services in which we can take pride, we need talented individuals to join our teams. With an equally diverse range of career options to match the enormous range of services we provide, we can help you develop your career and grow with Barts Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ghislaine Stephenson Ghislaine.stephenson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
